Document: TriangleMesh  
Path: godot/classes/class_trianglemesh.rst  
Summary: Methods for creating BVH trees from face data, retrieving geometry faces, and performing ray/segment intersection tests.  

Method: create_from_faces(faces: PackedVector3Array) → bool  
Creates the BVH tree from an array of faces. Each 3 vertices of the input faces array represent one triangle (face). Returns true if the tree is successfully built, false otherwise.  

Method: get_faces() → PackedVector3Array (const)  
Returns a copy of the geometry faces. Each 3 vertices of the array represent one triangle (face).  

Method: intersect_ray(begin: Vector3, dir: Vector3) → Dictionary (const)  
Tests for intersection with a ray starting at begin and facing dir, extending toward infinity. If an intersection occurs, returns a Dictionary with fields: position (intersection point), normal (triangle normal), face_index (triangle index). Returns an empty Dictionary if no intersection happens. See also intersect_segment(), which uses a finite-length segment.  

Method: intersect_segment(begin: Vector3, end: Vector3) → Dictionary (const)  
Tests for intersection with a segment from begin to end. Returns a Dictionary with position, normal, and face_index if an intersection occurs. Returns an empty Dictionary if no intersection happens. See also intersect_ray(), which uses an infinite-length ray.